Detailed Description

Bluetooth has defined some profiles like Head Set or Hands Free that are used to increase the comfort of handling the device. These profiles are called accessory profiles. To make the service search for such profiles easier the Bluetooth Stack has defined an operation that queries exactly this kind of profiles from Remote Bluetooth Devices. BtQuerySupportedProfilesRequest is the implementation of the operation described above.

BOOLEAN BtQuerySupportedProfilesRequest::Execute (   )  [protected, virtual]
 

Sumbit this request to the Bluetooth Stack.

ExecuteRequest instructs this request to send itself to the Bluetooth Stack for execution purposes.
In the base class of all Bluetooth Requests - BtRequest - there is an interface defined, that all requests must fullfill respectively implement. Some functions in this interface are declared pure virtual because they can not be implemented in the base classes. ExecuteRequest is one of these functions. Because the execution of various requests differ very strong, the implmentation of this function is done by the various concrete request classes.

Returns:
TRUE: The setup of the stack parameters was successfull and the Bluetooth stack accepted the requested operation.
FALSE: Either the setup of the stack parameters failed or the Bluetooth stack rejected the requested operation.

Implements BtRequest.

BtRequestType BtQuerySupportedProfilesRequest::GetRequestType (   )  const [virtual]
 

Get type of this request.

The runtime type information feature is not supported by all compilers which this framework is used with. So a rudimentary type information system is implemnted by this class. Each type of request that has no subtypes (leaf class) must return an unique type identifier. GetRuestType return this type idenifier which is implemented as an enumeration type.

A BtRequestType containing the type that describes this request.

void BtQuerySupportedProfilesRequest::OnHfProfileSupported (  const WString &  name,
UINT16  supported_features
)  [protected, virtual]
 

Hands free supported message handler member function.

The OnHfProfileSupported member function will be invoked when a BtHfProfileSupportedMessage is received by this request. This member function is used to enable some reaction to the receipt of the aforsaid message.
The implmenetation of this member function is a dummy implementation and does nothing. If the application programmer wants to change this behaviour, he has to overload this function in a derived class. He need not to call the inherited base function, because it does nothing.

Parameters:
name A reference to a WString containing the name of the hands free service.
supported_features An UINT16 containing the features as an bitfield that the hands free service supports.

BOOLEAN BtQuerySupportedProfilesRequest::OnMessage (  const Message &  message  )  [protected, virtual]
 

Message dispatching member function.

The OnMessage member function is the first entry point in every dispatcher for the reception of messages. From there on it will be routed to the appropriate On... member function, if it should be handled by this dispatcher or passed back to the superior dispatcher.

Returns:
TRUE: The received message has be handle. No further handling for the message is needed.
FALSE: The received message is not handled by this dispatcher. Route it forward to the next dispatcher.

void BtQuerySupportedProfilesRequest::RegisterMessages (   )  const [protected, virtual]
 

Register the required messages for receipt.

After registering itself at an application, the request has to tell the message dispatching mechanism which messages this request is intersted in. RegisterMessage performs this task. For the BtQuerySupportedProfilesRequest the following messages are registered: BtQuerySupportedProfilesMessage, BtHsSupportedProfileMessage, BtHfSupportedProfileMessage and BtPaSupportedProfileMessage.

Reimplemented from UserDispatcher.

void BtQuerySupportedProfilesRequest::UnregisterMessages (   )  const [protected, virtual]
 

Unregister the required messages from receipt.

Before unregistering itself from the application, the request has to remove the messages, it is interested in form the message dispatching mechanism. UnregisterMessage performs this task. For the BtQuerySupportedProfilesRequest the following messages are unregistered: BtQuerySupportedProfilesMessage, BtHsSupportedProfileMessage, BtHfSupportedProfileMessage and BtPaSupportedProfileMessage.

Reimplemented from UserDispatcher.
